    <h1>Working with Links, Images, and Multimedia</h1>

    <hr>

    <!-- LINKS -->
    <h2>1. Links</h2>
    <p><b>Usage:</b> Links are used to connect one webpage to another website or page.</p>
    <p><b>Explanation:</b> When a user clicks a link, it opens another webpage.</p>
    <p><b>Sample Activity:</b></p>
    <a href="https://www.google.com" target="_blank">Visit Google</a>

    <hr>

    <!-- IMAGES -->
    <h2>2. Images</h2>
    <p><b>Usage:</b> Images are used to display pictures on a website.</p>
    <p><b>Explanation:</b> Images help make the webpage more attractive and informative.</p>
    <p><b>Sample Activity:</b></p>
    <img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3f/Placeholder_view_vector.svg/512px-Placeholder_view_vector.svg.png"
         alt="Sample Image" width="200">

    <hr>

    <!-- MULTIMEDIA -->
    <h2>3. Multimedia</h2>
    <p><b>Usage:</b> Multimedia is used to add videos or audio to a webpage.</p>
    <p><b>Explanation:</b> Multimedia makes the website interactive for users.</p>
    <p><b>Sample Activity:</b></p>

    <video width="320" controls>
        <source src="https://www.w3schools.com/html/mov_bbb.mp4" type="video/mp4">
